text.tspan: This implementation of Personalised Page Rank follows the same
philosophy as a heat diffusion kernel. Nodes closer to the source or
target layers will receive a higher score than those further away, following
the assumption that the nodes closer to the measured nodes will be more
important in providing biological context compared to those far away.
The nodes can be then selected using a quantile threshold (e.g ~ N percent
of the nodes with highest PPR score)
